Of course! Here are some stretching exercises:
1. Neck Stretch: Tilt your head to one side, bringing your ear towards your shoulder, and hold for 15-30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.
2. Shoulder Stretch: Bring one arm across your body and gently press it towards your chest with the other hand. Hold for 15-30 seconds and switch sides.
3. Triceps Stretch: Reach one arm overhead and bend your elbow, placing your hand behind your neck. Use your other hand to gently press on your elbow. Hold for 15-30 seconds and switch sides.
4. Quadriceps Stretch: Stand on one leg and grab the ankle of your other leg behind you, gently pulling your heel towards your glutes. Hold for 15-30 seconds and switch legs.
5. Hamstring Stretch: Sit on the floor with one leg extended and the other bent so that the sole of your foot rests against your inner thigh. Lean forward from your hips and reach towards your toes. Hold for 15-30 seconds and switch legs.
Remember to breathe deeply and never bounce while stretching.
